==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[arcturus|arctūrus]]'' from {{Gr.}} '''[[Aρκτούρος]]''' (''Arktouros'') "bear guard", from '''[[άρκτος]]''' (''arktos'') "bear" + '''[[ούρος]]''' (''ouros'') "watcher, guardian", from '''[[hοράω]]''', '''[[hορώ]]''' (''horao'',''horo'') "to see, to look".

===Proper noun===
'''Arcturus'''

# {{star}} A bright yellow-orange [[star]] in the [[constellation]] [[Boötes]]; Alpha (α) Boötis. It is the third brightest star in the night sky.

